Gotify Hook Plugin for Opencode
================================

A plugin that sends notifications to Gotify when important events occur
in Opencode.

Setup
-----
Set the following environment variables:

  GOTIFY_URL          - Your Gotify server URL (e.g., https://gotify.example.com/message)
  GOTIFY_TOKEN        - Your Gotify application token
  GOTIFY_MIN_PRIORITY - (Optional) Minimum priority threshold (default: 5)

Priority
--------
Events are assigned numeric priorities (1-10). The plugin uses:
  - High (7): session.error, worktree.failed, mcp.browser.open.failed, pty.exited
  - Medium (5): question.asked, permission.asked, session.deleted, session.idle
  - Low (3): session.diff, session.created, vcs.branch.updated, question.rejected

The plugin defaults to GOTIFY_MIN_PRIORITY=5 (Balanced). 

To include all events (Verbose): Set GOTIFY_MIN_PRIORITY=0.
To only see high-priority events (Minimal): Set GOTIFY_MIN_PRIORITY=7.
